( ============================================================ )
( CARVERA SPINDLE CALIBRATION PROCEDURE )
( ============================================================ )
( 386 steps from 750 to 20000 RPM in 50 RPM increments )
( Each step holds for 0.25 seconds - firmware needs ~190ms )
(   (50ms speed-change settle + 80ms record + 60ms detection) )
( No M5 stops between steps - uses speed-change detection )
( Total time: ~7s start sequence + ~97s calibration = ~2 minutes )
( )
( The start sequence plays 3 zigzag tones (6000→12000→9000 RPM) via )
( speed changes. The firmware detects this pattern and enters cal mode. )
( ============================================================ )

( ======================== START SEQUENCE ======================== )
( Three zigzag tones via speed changes to trigger calibration mode )
( No M5 stops between notes - much faster than spin-up/down cycle )

M3 S6000
G4 P1
M3 S12000
G4 P1
M3 S9000
G4 P1
M5
G4 P1

( ====================== CALIBRATION STEPS ====================== )
( 386 steps: 750, 800, 850, ..., 20000 RPM )
( Speed changes directly - no M5 stops between steps )

